node.text: Switch off, settle in… and relax! 🙏 From @southaustralia’s surreal salt lakes to the inviting shores of @queensland’s @visitfraserisland, today we invite you to escape reality and soak up the serenity of our white-hued landscapes instead. Whether it’s a wombat wandering through #MtKosciuszko’s powdery alpine peaks or stunning @sydney harbour views, we’re certain you’ll find peace of mind whilst immersing yourself in the sounds and sights of our country via Australia in 8D.🕊️ Start planning your next relaxing getaway via the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: WHITE: A Moment of Peace - 8D Escapes

node.text: There’s no doubt about it, pink certainly suits Australia 💕 We couldn’t help but spread the love, or should we say, the lovely feeling, that these magical #magenta scenes from across our country invoke. Allow yourself a little time to marvel at the striking hues of @westernaustralia’s pink lake, take in the @visitgreatoceanroad and @australiasnorthwest's candy-coloured #sunset skies and savour the serenity of @tropicalnorthqueensland, as you fall head over heels with Australia in 8D 😍 To experience dreamy pastel-hued moments like this for yourself, head to the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: MAGENTA: A Moment of Freedom - 8D Escapes

node.text: Breathe in, breathe out … your tranquil adventure through our lush landscapes starts here 😌 Inspired by shades of green, today we’re transporting you to some of the most calming and captivating destinations across Australia, from @tropicalnorthqueensland's ancient rainforest and @rottnestislandwa’s quokka-filled shores, to the magnificent @visitbluemountains and ruggedly beautiful @ntaustralia. Sit back and immerse yourself in the raw and rejuvenating sights and sounds of Australia in 8D; we like to think of it as natural therapy, and relaxation is guaranteed 💚. For more inspiration on how to plan your next nature-based getaway, head to the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: GREEN: A Moment of Calm - 8D Escapes

node.text: While we know not everyone is able to travel here at the moment, we encourage you all, wherever you are, to keep dreaming of those bucket list destinations, secret escapes and once-in-a-lifetime experiences Australia has to offer. When it's safe, and the time is right, get out there and explore this big beautiful backyard of ours. #seeaustralia #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Today we’re rolling out Australia’s red carpet, just for you ❤️ Scarlet, cerise, ruby… call it what you like, it’s an unforgettable hue that can be found in abundance along the road less travelled in our big, bold and beautiful backyard. Take in the sights and sounds of the @ntaustralia’s aptly named #RedCentre and be amazed by the @australiasnorthwest #HorizontalFalls, via Australia in 8D. Feeling inspired to plan your own colourful adventure? Head to the link in our bio to discover more of Australia’s striking scenery. #seeaustralia

node.title: RED: A Moment of Escape - 8D Escapes

node.text: If you’re into mystery and thrills, step right this way... 🖤 There’s just something about @visitmelbourne’s sparkling city skyline and the pitter-patter of penguins exploring #PhillipIsland at dusk that leaves you wanting more. Feel the suspense that the patterns, textures and sounds of the @ngvmelbourne invoke, and allow your breath to be taken away by the sheer power of #KakaduNationalPark’s waterfalls in @ntaustralia. Elegant and bold, Australia’s landscapes with a touch of black demand to be seen and explored via Australia in 8D 😎 To create your own adventure inspired by this dark and mystical hue, click the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: Black: A Moment of Inspiration - 8D Escapes

node.text: From wide-open skies to vast expanses of sea, Australia’s many shades of blue are simply irresistible 💙 Today we’re inviting you to dip your toes into our calming oceans, picturesque pools and idyllic island shores. Play with Australian Sea Lions at #BairdBay in @southaustralia, discover the colourful wonders of the @gbrmarinepark, see dolphins surfing the sparkling waves of @AustraliasGoldenOutback, and listen in awe to whales singing in @visitfrasercoast. Now is the time to escape reality and soak up the blissful-blues of Australia in 8D. To discover more holiday ideas inspired by this refreshing hue, click the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: Blue: A Moment of Joy - 8D Escapes

Hear from @chrishemsworth and find out what these @australianopen tennis stars love about visiting us. 🎾💚 This special message played at the #AustralianOpen in @rodlaverarena this week, as the tournament rebrands as "Australia is Open" during the finals weekend to let everyone know that we are welcoming visitors to take a #HolidayHereThisYear. Each January, this exciting Grand Slam tournament draws #tennis fanatics and spectators from all over the world to @visitmelbourne, it's a must-do for anyone who loves sports, music, food and fun!

#seeaustralia #visitmelbourne #AusOpen #AustraliaisOpen

node.text: These cheeky locals know where to find the best seat in the house for a @hamiltonisland sunset 💜@twosometravellers perfectly captured the magic of @queensland's @whitsundaysqld. Known for its resident #cockatoos and spectacular views, #HamiltonIsland is the largest of the 74 islands that make up the #Whitsundays. No visit to 'Hamo' is complete without exploring the #GreatBarrierReef. Grab your snorkel and admire the famous rainbow coral up close, or cruise your way towards the white sands of the iconic #WhitehavenBeach ⛵ #seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #lovewhitsundays #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on September 14, 2021. May be an image of body of water and nature.

node.text: Sun ✅ Sand ✅ Boat ✅... aka, the perfect combo! @_roamingaus_ spent an idyllic day exploring the stunning coastal region of Hawks Nest on the @barringtoncoast. A 2.5-hour drive from @sydney in @visitnsw, this is a great spot to explore when travel permits. Ensure you pay a visit to Myall Lakes National Park with its coastal forests, pristine beaches and huge sand dune system, as well as Broughton Island, which has some of the best diving and snorkelling sites in #NewSouthWales and a vast array of wildlife including penguins, turtles and seabirds. #seeaustralia #barringtoncoast #lovensw #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on September 14, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text: That's one unique swimming pool 😉 According to @shessimplywell, "there’s something so magical about swimming in the icy cold waterhole of a gorge." Who's ready to give it a try? 🙋‍♀️ Home to the Arrernte people, this little slice of heaven is Redbank Gorge, nestled at the base of Mt Sonder or Rwetyepme (pronounced ‘roo-chip-ma’). Located in @visitcentralaus, and part of Tjoritja (West MacDonnell National Park), this near-permanent waterhole is a must-see when visiting this part of @ntaustralia. #seeaustralia #NTaustralia #RedCentreNT #holidayherethisyear

node.text: This is what 100 humpback whales hanging out looks like! 🤯 🐋 @davey_rogers was on board @sapphirecoastaladventures late last week when he captured this incredible footage of a 'mega-pod' in the @sapphirecoastnsw. This mind-blowing natural sight occurred off the coast of #Bermagui in @visitnsw and is believed to be only the second time a pod of this size has been filmed in Australian waters! The best time to see these gentle giants here is from September to November during their annual migration - spot them from the shore, or book a whale-watching cruise. #seeaustralia #sapphirecoast #lovensw #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on September 13, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text: When you realise your own backyard is pretty darn special 😍 The views on #MagneticIsland are that spectacular, even the locals stop and stare! @destinationadventureq captured this furry local enjoying all the #MagneticIslandRaceWeek action recently⛵ Located off the coast of @townsvillenorthqueensland in @queensland, palm-fringed beaches, cheeky wildlife and snorkelling adventures are just a few of the fabulous things you'll find on @thisismagneticisland. Set sail with @bigmamasailingnorthqueensland or @pilgrimsailing to enjoy the scenery for yourself. #seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #townsvilleshines #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Talk about a party wave 🐬 @jaimenhudson captured this amazing scene in @visitesperance, home to the Nyungar and Ngadju people. To really explore this incredible part of @westernaustralia, we recommend jumping in the car and embarking on the 40 kilometre Great Ocean Drive, which takes you past stunning beaches, rocky headlands, sea cliffs and hidden ocean pools. TIP: There are also amazing wildflowers to be found in this region from August through to November 🌸 #seeaustralia #thisisWA #visitesperance #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on September 12, 2021. May be an image of nature and body of water.

node.text: We're obsessed with the colours of #CapeYork 🧡 @timetohittheroad.p.k snapped this gorgeous shot of #ElimBeach, which is a must-visit if you're heading to this part of @tropicalnorthqueensland. You'll find this stunning stretch of coastline one-hour north of #Cooktown in @queensland. Pitch your tent at @eddiesbeachcampground, which is run by Thiithaarr-warra Elder, Eddie Deemal, and is the perfect base to explore the incredible coloured sands and vibrant cliffs. #seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #explorenq #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on September 11, 2021. May be an image of nature and ocean.

node.text: We can't help but fall a little bit more in love with @tourismtopend every time we see it 😍 Thanks to @pianemec, who captured this incredible shot of #DundeeBeach on a recent trip to @ntaustralia. Located an hour from #Darwin, @dundeebeach_holidaypark is a great spot to base yourself as you explore the Peninsula Way region, where you'll have pristine beaches, epic fishing, wildlife watching opportunities and sensational sunsets - all right at your fingertips. BRB, we're off to reconnect with nature! 🍃 #SeeAustralia #NTAustralia #TourismTopEnd #HolidayHereThisYear

node.text: Now, THIS is how we'd like to spend our spring days ☀️💦 @ellafreestone beautifully captured the gorgeous weather in Yuin Country (@sapphirecoastnsw). The sparkling blue waters of the Pambula River Mouth in @visitnsw are surrounded by national park, and perfectly sheltered from the wind and swell coming from the south. When travel permits, it's a kayaking, SUPing, and fishing paradise (and by the looks of it, the ideal place for a relaxing swim in the sun). #seeaustralia #SapphireCoast #lovensw #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on September 10, 2021. May be an image of flightless bird and nature.

node.text: Humans aren't the only ones who enjoy a good stroll along the beach, y'know 😜 @rafaelmenon spotted this elusive bird on a recent visit to @tropicalnorthqueensland's #EttyBay. Tucked away on the rugged #CassowaryCoast, if you're in the right place at the right time you might be lucky enough to see a Southern Cassowary, an impressive creature that is one of the closest living species to dinosaurs! If you're planning a trip to this stunning part of @queensland, make sure to rise early, as sightings are most common first thing in the morning. #seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #tropicalnorthqueensland #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on September 10, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text: Ah, @westernaustralia, you never cease to amaze us 🙌🏼 Kudos to @helen_jannesonbense & @bobbybense, who captured this epic shot of #YardieCreekGorge in @australiascoralcoast. Discover this colourful landscape in #CapeRangeNationalPark on a gorge walk with @salsalisningaloo, or onboard a boat tour with @ycbts. Be sure to keep your eyes peeled, as Yardie Creek is home to the rare black-footed wallaby, red kangaroos and an array of birdlife. #seeaustralia #australiascoralcoast #thisiswa #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on September 09, 2021. May be an image of animal and outdoors.

node.text: Those end of the week feels 💤🐨 @charley_geddes captured this sleepy fellow in the country town of Nebo in the @visitmackay region, home to the Yuwibara people. This part of @queensland is where you'll find Cape Hillsborough National Park, which is famous for its abundance of wildlife, including #koalas and the friendly wallabies and kangaroos that visit the beach each morning at sunrise. FACT: Koalas can sleep between 18 to 22 hours a day! They sleep a lot to conserve energy as the leaves they eat require a lot of energy to digest. #seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #visitmackay #holidayherethisyear
